-- HIGHLIGHTS-Bank of England's FPC tightens home loan rules
-- 
-- Thu Jun 26, 2014 05:43AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, June 26 (Reuters) - The Bank of England sought to slam the brakes on Britain's surging housing market on Thursday by announcing a cap on home loans and tougher checks on whether borrowers can repay their mortgages. [ID:nS8N0P000S]

Following are the highlights of press conference given by the bank's Financial Policy Committee, headed by bank governor Mark Carney:  CARNEY ON WHAT MEASURES WILL ACHIEVE: (These measures) will prevent lending getting too far ahead of income growth and they'll prevent a slide into riskier lending and higher indebtedness that could undermine the economic expansion over the medium term. (david.milliken@reuters.com; +44 20 7542 5109; Reuters Messaging: david.milliken.thomsonreuters.com@reuters.net)  Keywords: BRITAINHOUSING